<p>Volatility is influenced by market news, geopolitical events, central bank announcements and economic data releases from the Eurozone and the United States.</p>
<h2><strong>What are the Trading Time and Volatility Patterns?</strong></h2>
<p>The average daily movement of EUR/USD is around 57 pips over a 10-week period. The most active trading hours are from 1 PM to 4 PM GMT. Significant economic announcements, such as the US Non-Farm Payroll (NFP) data, can cause sharp movements.</p>
